      <hedline>
        <hl1>Homeless Children And Educational Needs</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jane Goldblatt disputes Joseph Sanacore's April 30 essay on providing educational services to homeless children (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Someone should welcome Mr. Sanacore to the real world. School districts would have to cope with the cost of providing his list of services.  And people are indifferent to the plight of the homeless. If they weren't, there wouldn't be a million homeless children in the country.</p>
        <p>JANE GOLDBLATT  East Northport</p>
      </block>
